author: ART KABELOWSKY | Wisconsin State Journal
title: Prep boys soccer: Madison West ranked No. 5 in Division 1 state coaches' poll
text:
Buy Now AMBER ARNOLD -- State Journal 
Madison Memorial's Christian Vitela (6) heads the ball with Madison West's Sam Loving, at left, in the first half of a Big Eight Conference boys soccer match at Mansfield Stadium in Madison, Wis., Tuesday, September 29, 2015. AMBER ARNOLD -- State Journal 
Madison West’s boys soccer team dipped one position to No. 5 in this week’s Wisconsin Soccer Coaches Association Division 1 state rankings. 
The Regents, 11-2-3 overall, lost 3-1 at unranked Brookfield Central on Saturday. West still stands two points behind Middleton (11-3-1) in the Big Eight Conference standings, and the Regents have one more league game to play than the Cardinals. 
Sun Prairie (9-2-4), Middleton and Beloit Memorial (17-4-1) each earned honorable mention in Division 1. 
In Division 2, Oregon (7-5-4) earned honorable mention. Mount Horeb (10-6-3) earned honorable mention in Division 3. 
The top-ranked teams were Milwaukee Marquette in Division 1, Whitefish Bay in Division 2, unbeaten and untied Delavan-Darien in Division 3 and University School of Milwaukee in Division 4. 
WISCONSIN SOCCER COACHES ASSOCIATION
